{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban the use of plastic packaging for all non-food items",
        "additional_details": "Plastic waste is both a public health and environmental issue. Wind-blown microplastics have been found in the placentas of pregnant mothers. The UK has a huge amount of coastline affected by plastic waste. On both counts it makes sense for us to give a lead globally. Plastic bans have proved effective in other countries. It is essential that we drastically reduce the production of new plastics and work towards an efficient, circular economy.\r\n\r\nMicroplastics in placentas:\r\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/dec/22/microplastics-revealed-in-placentas-unborn-babies\r\n\r\nMarine Conservation Society on plastics on UK Coast:\r\nhttps://www.mcsuk.org/clean-seas/microplastics",
        "background": "Plastic packaging is a global issue. Too many items are sold in non-recyclable, non-compostable plastic packaging. Alternatives such as paper and cardboard are perfectly viable for such items as children\u2019s toys, tools, office equipment, mobile devices, clothes, electrical goods and so on.",
